name: Tegal project
address: F37P+35M, Baturiti, Kerambitan, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82181, Indonesia
review 1:
We stayed here for 1 week as a couple and it was amazing. There are tents just at the lap of the nature. There are many coconut trees around and we have met many other foreigners.

Kadek & his girlfriend are really a very good host. Highly recommended if you are going Bali, must stay it visit this place.
You will also learn about organic farming and a lot about Balinese culture.
review 2:
Stayed at Tegal project in the first week of June...Enjoyed a lot with Kadek & his family..if you like nature and countryside then you will fall in love with this place. We did yoga, played games, went to waterfalls, and explored the real Bali.

I wish all the best for organic farming project. Recommended for backpackers & nature seekers.
review 3:
Great people who are giving a lot for the future of the children in the small villages.
The new Must-see place in Bali when u enjoy staying away from tourists!
If you are lucky you get the chance to see west Bali with its beautiful temples and beaches :) if you are not lucky with that you are still lucky because this place Is amazing to chill, to learn about the Balinese culture and how to cook :D
review 4: What an incredible place to visit! Kadek and his family were very welcoming and showed me many amazing places that I wouldn't have ever known about. I would recommend this to anyone who would like to experience the true beauty of Bali and learn about Balinese culture!
review 5: The best things what happened to me, it's happened in Tegal Project!
